properties.Title: Blowing Snow Advisory In Effect
properties.Summary:

properties.Title: Blizzard Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Blizzard conditions with poor visibility in snow and blowing snow are expected or occurring. Blizzard conditions are expected in Qikiqtarjuak today as a low pressure system over the Davis Strait moves towards the coast. Snow is expected to begin this morning with winds strengthening to northerly 60 gusting 80 km/h this afternoon giving near-zero visibility in blizzard conditions. Winds are forecast to diminish late this evening, but strengthen again on Wednesday with more snow and blowing snow in the forecast. ### Travel is expected to be hazardous due to reduced visibility. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NUstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NUStorm.

properties.Title: Blizzard Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Dangerous blizzard conditions are expected, with substantial amounts of snow and strong winds. Locations: central Labrador including Upper Lake Melville. Time span: continuing until near midnight tonight. Snowfall today: 30 to 50 cm, with the greatest amounts expected over higher terrain and along the Trans Labrador Highway between Crooks Lake and Kenamu River. Maximum wind gusts: north to northwesterly 80 to 90 km/h, except 100 along the Trans Labrador Highway through Eagle River this evening. Remarks: Snow, at times heavy, will continue through today before tapering off this evening. Visibilities near zero in blizzard conditions can be expected today as winds strengthen. The winds are expected to begin easing overnight tonight. ### Road closures are likely. Blizzard warnings are issued when widespread reduced visibilities of 400 metres or less are expected for at least 4 hours. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NLstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NLwx.
